detail.title: OmniFlix contributors out of the game. Increase validators set for 5 places
detail.description:
##OmniFlix contributors out of the game
Currently 5 OmniFlix validators outside of the active set despite the fact that they have delegations from OmniFlix team and|or foundation. These 5 validators were incentivized for participating in the testnets, providing RPC|REST endpoints, as well as analytical tools to the OmniFlix community. Here is the list: #76 - Wetez, #77 - NODEJUMPER, #78 - Architect Nodes, #79 - CosmosPug, #80 - 50% back. According to the proposal #10 that's was created for including the second part of testnet partisipants into the active set it's be fair to extend active set for 5 places for those OmniFlix contributors.
##Bottom line
If this proposal will pass the number of active validators will be changed from 75 to 80.
##Discussion
https://commonwealth.im/omniflix/discussion/13175-attempt-2-validators-seats-increment

detail.title: OmniFlix Hub v0.12.x Upgrade Proposal
detail.description:
## Overview
This governance proposal is presented for your consideration and approval of the proposed updates to the omniflixhub (upgrading the software version from v0.11.1 to v0.12.0).

## Upgrade name
v0.12.x

## Upgrade height
[8054200](https://www.mintscan.io/omniflix/blocks/8054200)

## Upgrade details

Proposed upgrade details are as follows:
1. Gas optimization within the ITC Module
2. Introducing PFM (packet forward middleware)
3. Enabling ICA host 
4. Refactored the app
5. Moved the `marketplace` module from it's own repo to the `omniflixhub/x` folder


## Upgrade instructions
Upgrade guide:
[https://github.com/OmniFlix/docs/blob/main/guides/mainnet/omniflixhub-1/upgrades/v0.12.x-upgrade.md](https://github.com/OmniFlix/docs/blob/main/guides/mainnet/omniflixhub-1/upgrades/v0.12.x-upgrade.md)

Release tag:
[https://github.com/OmniFlix/omniflixhub/releases/tag/v0.12.0](https://github.com/OmniFlix/omniflixhub/releases/tag/v0.12.0)


## Voting

The opinion of the community is highly valued. All stakeholders are invited to vote on this proposal. The voting options are as follows:

- **Yes**: Agreement with the proposed updates and a desire for their implementation.
- **No**: Disagreement with the proposed updates and a preference against their implementation.
- **Abstain**: A choice not to vote on the proposal.
- **NoWithVeto**: A strong disagreement with the proposed updates and a desire to veto them.

All stakeholders are encouraged to participate in the voting process. Each vote matters and will help shape the future of the OmniFlix Hub.

detail.title: Increase total active validators from 75 to 80
detail.description:
### Summary

If this proposal passes the active validator set will increase from 75 active validators to 80 active validators.

### Description

This proposal will increase the number of active validator to 80 in the Omniflix. The last update was done before 3 months, and it was already mentioned that the network could easily assume 80 active seats. 

We propose to add 5 seats on the main chain. A lot of new validators are building on the omniflix but not directly as they cannot afford to join the mainnet to have an active seat. We believe at ApeironNodes that every builder on the omniflix should be able to provide an active validating service to maintain atleast a small percentage of the running costs.

### Voting

Vote YES on the proposal if you are in favor of increasing the active set from 75 validators to 80 validators
Vote NO on the proposal if you are NOT in favor of increasing the active set from 75 validators to 80 validators
Vote ABSTAIN on the proposal if you intend to refrain from participating in the proposal
Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this as a harmful proposal to the future of the network

### Proposer & Signer
Panvasi | ApeironNodes

detail.title: Signalling Proposal - Transfer tokens to initiate the FlixDrop
detail.description:
## **Overview**

FlixDrop is a token distribution mechanism designed to reward active stakeholders across the OmniFlix ecosystem.

With participation from Cosmonauts across 32 categories, FlixDrop aims to recognize and incentivize all the contributors, stakeholders, partners and community members.

As per the tokenomics published on [Mirror.xyz](https://mirror.xyz/omniflixnetwork.eth/ofhbzvUBx5WjrrGyNWHSnGYFDA3NtnmIGko16cxYG4M) the 60M FLIX reserved for the FlixDrop will be utilized in multiple phases.

This signalling proposal covers the transfer of 60M FLIX allocated for the FlixDrop to active stakeholders within the OmniFlix ecosystem. Of this 35M FLIX will be used to create campaigns using the Interact-to-Claim module across 32 categories of the FlixDrop.

Additionally, 10M FLIX is reserved for future drops to expand across ecosystems, and 15M FLIX is earmarked for DAO2DAO collaborations, fostering network-wide cooperation.

## **Proposal Details**

- Allocation:
  - 35M FLIX tokens for the initial FlixDrop distribution to active stakeholders.
  - 10M FLIX tokens for future drops to extend FlixDrop's reach.
  - 15M FLIX tokens for collaborative initiatives with DAOs.

## **Multisig Details**

- Multisig Accounts:
	-  35M FLIX will be transferred to `omniflix1zpy8796kmfwulx3x8kf9mylryze0r9f6nvgr4x`
	- 10M FLIX will be transferred to `omniflix18n2qu9xyn3u4v9mfnm6j45ztrenp5m2yaetukj`
	- 15M FLIX will be transferred to `omniflix19x50aq596a9ukqwkhtterp850dw8ygdl4ma5rx`

- Key Stakeholder as a signer of the Multisig
  - Daya (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)
  - Harish (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)
  - Rambabu (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)

## **Voting Options**
Please note the slight change in the options if you haven't followed the conversation on Discord.

- Vote YES to support the proposal and initiate the execution of FlixDrop operations upon reaching quorum.
- Vote NO to reject the proposal.
- Vote ABSTAIN to abstain from participating in the voting process.
- Vote NO WITH VETO if you believe the proposal has detrimental effects on the network's future.

Your active participation and feedback are crucial to shaping the future of the OmniFlix ecosystem. Let's work together to ensure the success and widespread engagement of FlixDrop. Thank you for your contribution.

Commonwealth Thread: https://commonwealth.im/omniflix/discussion/12134-signalling-proposal-transfer-tokens-to-initiate-the-flixdrop

detail.title: OmniFlix Hub Upgrade v0.11.0 Proposal
detail.description:
## Overview
This governance proposal is presented for your consideration.

These are updates to the OmniFlix Hub modules where the core binary version is being updated from `v0.10.x` to `v0.11.0`.

This release is anticipated to better enhance the performance and capabilities of the network updating older modules and introducing new modules.

## Upgrade name
v0.11.0

## Upgrade height
[7339200](https://www.mintscan.io/omniflix/blocks/7339200)

## Upgrade details

Proposed upgrade details are as follows:

### Dependency bumps

1. **`Cosmos SDK`:** The Cosmos SDK version will be updated from v0.45.15 to v0.45.16, which includes a bug fix for feegrants.

2. **`IBC`:** The IBC module’s version will be upgraded from v3.4.0 to 4.4.2, enabling the support of the latest IBC protocols and including the huckleberry batch for the IBC module.

3. **`CometBFT`:** The CometBFT module will be updated from v0.34.27 to v0.34.28.

### Updates to current modules on OmniFlix Hub

1. **`onft`:** The `onft` module will be updated from version v0.5 to 0.6, which includes updates for `events` that provide additional functionality and flexibility to developers, benefiting creators and their communities.

2. **`marketplace`:** The `marketplace` module will be updated from v0.4.1 to v0.6.0. This update aims to modify bid processing functionality for a better auction experience for creators and collectors. It also adds a new parameter,`maximum auction duration`, to restrict the creation of auctions with ultra-long durations.

### New Modules

1. **`itc`**
    - `itc`, or Interact-to-Claim, is a module for creators and communities to create campaigns.
    - Campaigns take the input of an NFT from an eligible collection and process a `claim` after an`interaction`, which can be one of Burn, Transfer, or Verify.
    - Participants that interact and claim receive rewards that are either NFTs or fungible tokens or both.
    - The Interact to Claim module allows for engaging community members using fungible tokens or NFTs and fosters collaborations among various creators and their communities.
    
2. **`streampay`**
    - StreamPay is a programmable protocol for creating payment streams where one account transfers tokens to another account in a time-based format. This transfer in a time-based format supports 3 types of Payment Streams:
        - Continuous: The claim is always active as tokens get streamed every second.
        - Periodic: The claim is active when there are tokens to claim and can be periodic in nature, i.e., tokens are streamed every hour, day, or even weeks.
        - Delayed: Tokens are streamed at the end of a specific time, similar to a scheduled transfer of tokens.

## Upgrade instructions
Upgrade guide:
[https://github.com/OmniFlix/docs/blob/main/guides/mainnet/omniflixhub-1/upgrades/v0.11.0-upgrade.md](https://github.com/OmniFlix/docs/blob/main/guides/mainnet/omniflixhub-1/upgrades/v0.11.0-upgrade.md)

Release tag:
[https://github.com/OmniFlix/omniflixhub/releases/tag/v0.11.0](https://github.com/OmniFlix/omniflixhub/releases/tag/v0.11.0)

## Voting

The opinion of the community is highly valued. All stakeholders are invited to vote on this proposal. The voting options are as follows:

- **Yes**: Agreement with the proposed updates and a desire for their implementation.
- **No**: Disagreement with the proposed updates and a preference against their implementation.
- **Abstain**: A choice not to vote on the proposal.
- **NoWithVeto**: A strong disagreement with the proposed updates and a desire to veto them.

All stakeholders are encouraged to participate in the voting process. Each vote matters and will help shape the future of the OmniFlix Hub.

Interact with the community on:
- [Twitter](https://twitter.com/OmniFLixNetwork)
- [Discord](https://discord.com/invite/6gdQ4yZSTC)
- [Telegram](https://t.me/OmniFlixChat)

detail.title: oNFT Param Change: Decreasing the collection fee from 100FLIX to 25FLIX
detail.description:
## Abstract 
 This proposal suggests adjusting the NFT collection creation fee on the OmniFlix platform from the current 100 FLIX to a more manageable 25 FLIX. This adjustment reflects the recent increase in the value of FLIX and aims to maintain accessibility for new creators.

 ## Overview
 With the launch of the FLIX token, an NFT collection creation fee of 100 FLIX was implemented to deter spam collections and preserve the quality of projects launched on the ecosystem. As the value of FLIX has increased, so has this fee in USD terms, which could deter new creators. This proposal aims to balance the need for spam deterrence with accessibility for creators.

 ## Proposal Details
 The proposed reduction in the NFT collection creation fee from 100 FLIX to 25 FLIX is based on the current FLIX value. This adjustment will still be subject to community debate due to the potential volatility of the FLIX token.
 It is suggested that this is a temporary measure. A future proposal could consider pegging the FLIX collection creation fee to a fixed USD value via an oracle or similar mechanism, to prevent the fee from drifting too far from a community-agreed value. This would also avoid the need for governance adjustments each time the fee needs to be revised.

 ## Future Considerations
 In addition to regular reviews of this fee, future proposals could consider initiatives for new creators experiencing financial hardship, such as loans or grants, to cover the initial cost of the collection creation process. This would ensure only committed artists enter the ecosystem, while also providing opportunities for those who need them. 

 ## Summary
 The proposed adjustment for the OmniFlix NFT collection creation fee is as follows:
 Current Fee: 100 FLIX
 Proposed Fee: 25 FLIX

 ## Community Discussion for Reference
 Please follow the link to join the discussion: (Commonwealth)[https://commonwealth.im/omniflix/discussion/11310-draft-signaling-proposal-to-adjust-the-nft-collection-creation-fee]

detail.title: Increase total active validators from 64 to 75
detail.description:
Smart Stake, as a proud validator & contributor to the OmniFlix Network, intends to express our gratitude to all fellow validators who've been running nodes and supporting the network for over a year.

Throughout the year, OmniFlix has attracted interest and contributions from teams running validators but not all of us were a part of the genesis validator set. Expanding the active validator set offers more opportunities for everyone contributing to the OmniFlix Hub and increases network decentralization.

Initially, the validator set comprised 64 active validators. The network was bootstrapped by issuing 10 FLIX to validators at genesis. Validators joining after the mainnet launched in Feb 2022, received fewer FLIX, which restricted their entry into the active set.

With this proposal, the ask is to increase the active set, bring on-board further validators and contributors and increase decentralization of voting power  

### Voting Options:
 - Vote YES on the proposal if you are in favor of increasing the active set from 64 validators to 75 validators
- Vote NO on the proposal if you are NOT in favor of increasing the active set from 64 validators to 75 validators
- Vote ABSTAIN on the proposal if you intend to refrain from participating in the proposal
- Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this as a harmful proposal to the future of the network

detail.title: Enable Inflation
detail.description:
## Abstract
This proposal suggests setting the inflation parameters for the OmniFlix Hub. The parameters for minimum and maximum inflation will be set at 32.5% and 33% respectively, with a change rate of 0.005.

## Overview
The minimum and maximum inflation parameters are critical in maintaining the stability of the OmniFlix Hub network. The proposed parameters will allow for a range of inflation rates that will adjust based on the bonded ratio (total tokens staked). The change rate will determine the rate of change in inflation based on the bonded ratio.

If the total bonded tokens exceed 67%, the inflation rate will decrease, as most of the delegators will have delegated their voting power and the network is deemed secure enough from an economic attack. If the total bonded tokens are below 67%, the inflation rate will increase to incentivize delegation of voting power to increase it up to the threshold of 67%.

## Future updates to inflation
Parameters will be updated to adhere to the tokenomics as required after or within the year. Further measures will be undertaken to avoid periodic updates.

Tokenomics of the FLIX token — https://mirror.xyz/omniflixnetwork.eth/ofhbzvUBx5WjrrGyNWHSnGYFDA3NtnmIGko16cxYG4M

## Summary
The proposed parameters for the OmniFlix Hub inflation are as follows:
 - Minimum Inflation: 32.5%
 - Maximum Inflation: 33%
 - Change Rate: 0.005

messages.title: Enable Inflation
messages.description:
## Abstract
This proposal suggests setting the inflation parameters for the OmniFlix Hub. The parameters for minimum and maximum inflation will be set at 32.5% and 33% respectively, with a change rate of 0.005.

## Overview
The minimum and maximum inflation parameters are critical in maintaining the stability of the OmniFlix Hub network. The proposed parameters will allow for a range of inflation rates that will adjust based on the bonded ratio (total tokens staked). The change rate will determine the rate of change in inflation based on the bonded ratio.

If the total bonded tokens exceed 67%, the inflation rate will decrease, as most of the delegators will have delegated their voting power and the network is deemed secure enough from an economic attack. If the total bonded tokens are below 67%, the inflation rate will increase to incentivize delegation of voting power to increase it up to the threshold of 67%.

## Future updates to inflation
Parameters will be updated to adhere to the tokenomics as required after or within the year. Further measures will be undertaken to avoid periodic updates.

Tokenomics of the FLIX token — https://mirror.xyz/omniflixnetwork.eth/ofhbzvUBx5WjrrGyNWHSnGYFDA3NtnmIGko16cxYG4M

## Summary
The proposed parameters for the OmniFlix Hub inflation are as follows:
 - Minimum Inflation: 32.5%
 - Maximum Inflation: 33%
 - Change Rate: 0.005

## Voting Options
Validators can choose from the following voting options:

Vote YES to agree with the proposal
Vote NO to reject the proposal
Vote ABSTAIN to refrain from choosing a decisive option but to support the majority
Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this as a harmful proposal to the future of the network

detail.title: Signalling Proposal to allocate 10M FLIX for LP incentives
detail.description:
Proposal draft for the Allocation of 10M FLIX for Liquidity Provider Incentives

# Overview
Liquidity is an essential aspect of any decentralized network, and it is crucial for the OmniFlix Hub ecosystem to have sufficient liquidity for the growth and success of the network. In this proposal, and as per the [tokenomics][1] an allocation of **10M FLIX** tokens from the Community Bootstrapping Allocation is allocated towards liquidity provider incentives for the OmniFlix Hub. These incentives will help bootstrap liquidity on the network right from day 1, and will ultimately contribute to the growth and success of the network.

## Proposal Details:
The proposed allocation of 10M FLIX tokens from the current reserve towards liquidity provider incentives will be used to incentivize liquidity providers on various DEXs like Osmosis, WYND, Crescent, Kujira, and more. Of these, the first set of incentives go live on Osmosis and further incentives will be discussed with respective DEX/protocol teams.

The exact distribution percentages will be decided based on the network's token economics and will be made available to the community before the distribution. Note that only a percentage of tokens will be utilized and the entire 10M FLIX budget will be spread out and will be used for incentives over a period of time.

## Multisig Details
The funds are proposed to be transferred to a multisig account, managed by:
- Daya (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)
- Harish (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)
- Rambabu (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)

Multisig Account - **omniflix1qquszwmyk9ewu4yshanyqualks39e52exduemq**

## Voting Options:
Validators are requested to carefully review this proposal and provide feedback to the community on Commonwealth and Discord. Validators are also requested to participate in the voting process by choosing from the following options:
- Vote YES to agree with the proposal
- Vote NO to reject the ideas in the proposal
- Vote ABSTAIN to refrain from participation
- Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this as a harmful proposal to the future of the network.

[1]: https://mirror.xyz/omniflixnetwork.eth/ofhbzvUBx5WjrrGyNWHSnGYFDA3NtnmIGko16cxYG4M

detail.title: Signalling proposal to allocate and transfer FLIX to the multisig for the token launch via StreamSwap on Osmosis
detail.description:
Hello Fam!

Below is the draft proposal to signal for the use of funds for the StreamSwap stream.

# Abstract
This is a proposal to signal the transfer of 5M FLIX tokens from the current reserves for the token launch via StreamSwap.

As outlined in the FLIX tokenomics article available on the URL below.

Tokenomics URL — https://mirror.xyz/omniflixnetwork.eth/ofhbzvUBx5WjrrGyNWHSnGYFDA3NtnmIGko16cxYG4M

This is ~1.6% of the Supply that will be utilized for the economic (token) launch via StreamSwap Protocol on Osmosis.

# Overview
According to the FLIX tokenomics, a total of 5M FLIX have been allocated for the StreamSwap stream. Below is the break down:
- 1M FLIX will be utilized for first stream. This stream will accept OSMO for the FLIX being streamed.
- 10% has been reserved for StreamSwap participation incentives in various ways (i.e. 500,000 FLIX)
- The rest will be used exclusively for StreamSwap streams immediately or over a period of time.
- The community will be informed of all the details via posts on the web3 publication, mirror.xyz/omniflixnetwork.eth and our social accounts.

## Use of proceeds
- All proceeds from the StreamSwap streams will be received by the treasury multi-sig account on Osmosis
- 50% will be used for liquidity &
- 50% will be sent to the Foundation for capitalization

The 50% being used for liquidity will be considered as protocol-owned-liquidity (POL), and rewards received will be utilized for further incentivization of LPs (across DEXs) to build increased liquidity for the FLIX token.

## Multisig Account Details
The funds are proposed to be transferred to a multisig account, managed by:
- Daya (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)
- Harish (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)
- Rambabu (core contributor OmniFlix Hub)

Multisig Account - **omniflix1yxgca3xgw6ngmh6xrcpfhjnau2alsq8jvuyt9u**

## Participation Details
Validators & related stakeholders are requested to review the proposal and vote accordingly. The voting options include:
- Vote YES on the proposal if you are in favor of transferring the 5M for StreamSwap to the multisig for stream creation
- Vote NO on the proposal if you are NOT in favor of transferring the 5M for StreamSwap to the multisig for stream creation
- Vote ABSTAIN on the proposal if you intend to refrain from participating.
- Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this as a harmful proposal to the future of the network.

detail.title: OmniFlix v0.10.0 upgrade
detail.description:
## Overview
Keeping with the commitment to continuously improve the blockchain, several important changes are being proposed as part of the v0.10.0 upgrade. These changes are aimed at making the network more secure & efficient while reducing spam.
## Upgrade name
v0.10.0

## Upgrade height
[6262420](https://www.mintscan.io/omniflix/blocks/6262420)

## Upgrade details
The proposed upgrade will contain the following changes:
### 1) oNFT updates
The oNFT module will be updated to include a collection creation fee (denom_creation_fee) to prevent spam and curate the creation of high-quality NFT collections. The version of oNFT to be included as a part of this upgrade is v0.5.0.
### 2) Gov updates
A minimum number of FLIX are required to for the initial deposit for the submitProposal transaction. This means that 10% of the minDeposit amount will have to be sent with the submit-proposal transaction and will most likely prevent spam proposals from being created on-chain.
### 3) Alloc module update
Weighted receiver multisig addresses (managed by subDAOs) for nft_incentives and node_host incentives will be added in the alloc module. The distribution percentages will be updated according to the token economics.
URL : https://mirror.xyz/omniflixnetwork.eth/ofhbzvUBx5WjrrGyNWHSnGYFDA3NtnmIGko16cxYG4M

### 4) Minor updates (and dependency bumps)
Cosmos SDK to be updated to v0.45.15
Tendermint to be updated to v0.34.27 (CometBFT)
Update ibc-go version to v3.4.0 from v3.3.1

The latest version of the Cosmos SDK, CometBFT and other packages will be updated to ensure that the OmniFlix Hub remains up-to-date with the latest security features and enhancements.

**NOTE:** The details of the exact binary will be shared during the course of the week after testing. Planning to publish the proposal to ensure that the update is completed before the FLIX token launch on 4/20 (20th of April).

## Upgrade instructions
upgrade guide:
[https://github.com/OmniFlix/docs/blob/main/guides/mainnet/omniflixhub-1/upgrades/v0.10.0-upgrade.md](https://github.com/OmniFlix/docs/blob/main/guides/mainnet/omniflixhub-1/upgrades/v0.10.0-upgrade.md)
release tag:
[https://github.com/OmniFlix/omniflixhub/releases/tag/v0.10.0](https://github.com/OmniFlix/omniflixhub/releases/tag/v0.10.0)

## Conclusion
The proposed v0.10.0 upgrade is aimed at making the OmniFlix Hub more secure, efficient, and user-friendly. Validators are requested to carefully review this proposal and provide feedback to the community on Commonwealth and Discord.
Validators are also requested to participate in the voting process by choosing from the following options when the proposal is issued on-chain:
Vote YES to agree with the proposal
Vote NO to reject the ideas in the proposal
Vote ABSTAIN to refrain from participation
Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this as a harmful proposal to the future of the network.

detail.title: OmniFlix Hub v0.8.0 with min. validator commission, auctions & more
detail.description:
## OmniFlix Hub v0.8.0 with min. validator commission, auctions & more
With this update, users can observe feature updates like Timed Reserve Auctions (part of the **marketplace** module) and minimum validator commission hard coded at 5% (future updates will include governance being able to update this) along with other security updates.
A note on the minimum validator commission. This is a feature implemented to avoid a race to 0% commission. This way, validator commission can not be used as a marketing differentiator which will in turn promote further decentralize the network.

## Details
The release features the below updates to the current binary:
* cosmos-sdk v0.45.10
* tendermint v0.34.22
* ibc-go v3.3.1
* marketplace v0.4.0 (auctions)

# Testing
The binary has been run by over 20 mainnet validators and over 5 testnet-only validators. Validators on the FlixNet-4 testnet voted on a proposal to initiate the upgrade at a specific block height.
From a front-end and user experience standpoint, the updates have been tested on the FlixNet-4 over 16,000 accounts participated in the incentivized testnet campaign to try out collection creation, NFT minting, listing via auctions, bidding on others’ auctions and activities around depositing IBC tokens.

## Instructions & release details
Instruction:https://github.com/OmniFlix/docs/blob/main/guides/mainnet/omniflixhub-1/upgrades/upgrade_1.md
**Important!** Please note to update iavl configuration in the app.toml file before restarting the node: iavl-disable-fastnode = false
Upgrade height: [4175400](https://www.mintscan.io/omniflix/blocks/4175400)
